# Context Compaction Hook

## Activation

This rule applies when the user says any of:
- "summarize this chat"
- "compact the context"
- "compress this conversation"
- "create a new chat with context"
- "hand off to a new session"
- "save what we've done"

## Process

### 1. Summarize + Compact in Parallel
Launch **both** agents simultaneously using two Task tool calls in a single message:
- **Summarize agent** — follows the `/summarize-chat` command to produce a structured summary of the conversation (goals, decisions, file changes, open items) and saves it to `.specstory/summaries/`.
- **Compact agent** — follows the `/compact-context` command to independently gather project state from git and `.specstory/history/`, then produces a dense briefing document and saves it to `.specstory/context/`.

Both agents work from the same source material (conversation history, git state, specstory history) so neither depends on the other's output. Wait for both to finish before proceeding.

### 2. Generate Deeplink and Auto-Open

After saving the compacted context, generate a Cursor deeplink and **open it automatically** via shell:

```bash
node -e "const text = 'Read the project briefing at .specstory/context/<date>-compact.md — this contains the full context from the previous session. Read it completely before doing anything else, then ask me what to work on next.'; const url = new URL('cursor://anysphere.cursor-deeplink/prompt'); url.searchParams.set('text', text); console.log(url.toString());"
```

Then immediately open it:

- Windows (PowerShell): `Start-Process "cursor://anysphere.cursor-deeplink/prompt?text=..."`
- macOS: `open "cursor://anysphere.cursor-deeplink/prompt?text=..."`
- Linux: `xdg-open "cursor://anysphere.cursor-deeplink/prompt?text=..."`

This launches a new Cursor chat pre-filled with the handoff prompt — no manual clicking required.

### 3. Confirm to the User
After opening, briefly tell the user:
- Where the summary and context files were saved
- That a new chat was opened with the context loaded

## Proactive Trigger

If you notice the conversation has gone on for a very long time (many exchanges, multiple complex tasks completed), suggest compaction:

> "This session has covered a lot of ground. Want me to summarize and compact the context so you can continue in a fresh chat without losing anything?"
